Swiss Banks May Face ‘Substantial’ Italian Outflows, T-A Says

-- B y   G i l e s   B r o o m
-- 
2011-09-12T06:28:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/swiss-banks-may-face-substantial-italian-outflows-t-a-says.html
Swiss banks may face “substantial
amounts” of outflows under a possible new tax settlement with
Italy, Alfredo Gysi, head of the Association of Foreign Banks in
 Switzerland  was cited as saying in an interview with the Zurich-
based  Tages-Anzeiger  newspaper.  There is a growing awareness that a withholding tax on
Italian assets banked in Switzerland is a good solution, Gysi
was cited as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Giles Broom in Geneva at 
 gbroom@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly in Paris at 
 fconnelly@bloomberg.net  